properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 6 at 3:42PM PST until January 8 at 12:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow will continue above 4000 feet. Additional snow
accumulations from 6 inches to as much as 3 feet for elevations
above 5000 feet.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis
Counties, including the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on
Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...Until midnight PST Tuesday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow may transition to a rain/snow mix
tonight into Tuesday for White Pass. The Northwest Avalanche
Center expects high avalanche danger to continue through Tuesday
with dangerous conditions through Wednesday. Check nwac.us for
the latest avalanche conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT PST TUESDAY NIGHT ABOVE 4000 FEET
